The paper focuses on object discovery and localization using pre-trained convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of data mining techniques also suggests a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves pattern mining, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
